Alliance Trust Shares Fall After Exclusion From FTSE 100 Index

-- B y   P e t e r   W o o d i f i e l d
-- 
2011-03-10T09:52:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/alliance-trust-shares-fall-after-exclusion-from-ftse-100-index.html
  Alliance Trust Plc (ATST)  shares declined
after the  FTSE Group  said late yesterday the Scottish closed-end
fund will be removed from its benchmark index.  The shares were down 3.6 pence, or 1 percent, to 354.4
pence at 9:44 a.m. in  London , valuing the fund at 2.34 billion
pounds ($3.78 billion). The Dundee-based fund has risen 9
percent in the past six months.  Alliance Trust will drop out of the FTSE 100 Index at the
end of trading on March 18. Wood Group Plc, an Aberdeen,
Scotland-based energy services group, will join the index on
March 21. Wood Group shares were down 6.5 pence, or 1 percent,
to 648.5 pence, valuing the company at 3.4 billion pounds. The
stock has surged 68 percent in the past six months.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Woodifield in Edinburgh at 
 pwoodifield@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at   ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 